I don't really see it getting any information. This isn't much of a commit msg. 

Can you update this to say something more like (I spent just a few mins writing, feel free to use but it can be further enhanced. Please take the time to write a good commit msg. :) ).

"Implements PowerSupply schema

This commit implements the Redfish PowerSupply schema and populates the PowerSupplyCollection members. The PowerSupply is a grandchild of the PowerSubsystem. PowerSupply is part of the new PowerSubsystme/ThermalSubsystem schemas, released in Redfish Version 2020.4. 

This commit only displays the PowerSupplies in the chassis with common fields like odata.id, odata.type, Id, and Name. Future commits will add PowerSupply properties like FirmwareVersion, LocationIndicatorActive, Status, and Asset information like SerialNumber, PartNumber, Model.

This commit looks at the powered_by association from Inventory.Item.Chassis to Inventory.Item.PowerSupply to find a PowerSupply. 

[1] https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/+/57428"

On 2nd look, I think this needs to be ResourceNotFound here because what if you don't have any /powered_by but the user requested to /redfish/v1/Chassis/<str>/PowerSubsystem/PowerSupplies/<str>/, that should be a resourceNotFound
getAssociationEndPoints returns 0 when there are no associations. At line 280, we are checking if the endpoints vector is empty, and logging an error in that case.

LOG_ERROR shouldn't be here since it will LOG for the resourceNotFound. Put in the if != EBADR? 

https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/blob/master/DEVELOPING.md#logging-levels
Typically the LOG ERROR is before the internal error, this is just for consistency in the journal, oh well
